Mr Wickham had to call on the help of East Sussex Fire Brigade which then lifted the van up to free the animal.

But the mischievous creature did not want to be caught and raced to a van parked in front where he hid again.

Luckily, Mr Wickham managed to coax him out before he got stuck again. 

Mr Wickham said: 'Badgers are nocturnal creatures so they like to be in dark places.

