Local photographer Eddie Mitchell was on hand to capture the reluctant rescue.

He said: 'The RSPCA thought it was going to be a simple rescue but this was quite a shrewd badger.

'He legged it. He did put up a little bit of a fight. He was a cheeky little so and so.'

The badger was not hurt and will be released back into the wild by the RSPCA this evening.

